    <modellingAndValidation>
      <representativeness systemModelId="290c1f85-4cc4-4fa1-b0c8-2cb7f4276dce" percent="81.0">
        <systemModelName xml:lang="en">Allocation, cut-off by classification</systemModelName>
        <samplingProcedure xml:lang="en">The data is compiled based on different data sources, including sustainability reports, literature values and expert judgements. Most data is derived from sustainability reports of the three principal concrete producers of Colombia (Argos, Cemex and Holcim). The data is checked, completed and validated by local experts. In total, it is estimated that the data considered is representative for 81% of cement production in all the country (market share of the three main cement producers). Unit flows were calculated by dividing the amounts of inputs and outputs by the total clinker production in mass. The amount of the exchanges were calculated considering the arithmetic [weighted] average of the sample. No conversion to the geometric mean of the lognormal distribution was done, for consistency reasons with other Ecoinvent datasets.</samplingProcedure>
        <extrapolations xml:lang="en">The life cycle inventory model is based on the PCR for cement and concrete (Environdec, 2010), as well as on the LCA core model of the WBCSD-CSI EPD tool (Dauriat et al., 2014). Dauriat, A., Porté, C., Delerce, C., Guignard, C., &amp; Adams, A. (2014). WBCSD CSI tool for EPDs of concrete and cement: LCA core model and database report. Environdec. (2010). Product category rules of UN CPC 3744 Cement.</extrapolations>
      </representativeness>
      <review reviewedMajorRelease="3" reviewedMinorRelease="0" reviewedMajorRevision="0" reviewedMinorRevision="6" reviewerId="44a0bdd8-6624-4a73-a661-7190ddf070b3" reviewerName="David FitzGerald" reviewerEmail="fitzgerald@ecoinvent.org" reviewDate="2022-08-04">
